, 
<collectingCountry box="[605,670,223,247]" name="Palau" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Palau</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[681,857,223,247]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, Great Barrier Reef, 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1309,223,247]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1432,223,247]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,263,260,284]" name="Mauritius" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[321,459,260,284]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,296,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
The second author observed one individual of this species at 
<quantity box="[998,1054,295,319]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="28.0">28 m</quantity>
while ascending from a deep dive off Jeddah in 
<number box="[302,360,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="1981.0">1981</number>
, with no bottom time remaining to collect the fish. He returned to the same area the next day, but failed to find the species. The present Red Sea record is based on the underwater photograph of a subadult (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1428,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[189,1409,942,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1410,942,1754]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bodianus bimaculatus, subadult, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia (R. Field)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[1413,1428,367,391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) taken off Jeddah by Richard Field. 
<figureCitation box="[543,636,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1620,1643]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,733,1598]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,733,1599]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Bodianus bimaculatus, Mauritius (J. E. Randall)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202774/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Figure 
<number box="[622,636,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
provides a photograph of an adult taken in 
<collectingCountry box="[1121,1234,404,428]" name="Mauritius" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. The color pattern of 
<figureCitation box="[181,275,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[189,1409,942,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1410,942,1754]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bodianus bimaculatus, subadult, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia (R. Field)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Figure 
<number box="[261,275,439,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
is approximately intermediate to that of a juvenile from 
<collectingCountry box="[910,974,440,463]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Japan</collectingCountry>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gomon" box="[1134,1300,439,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Gomon, M. F. (2006) A revision of the labrid fish genus Bodianus. Records of the Australian Museum, suppl. 30, 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="2006">
Gomon (
<number box="[1233,1292,439,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as Plate I C and the initial-phase adult from Bali of his Plate I D. An underwater photo of one from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1190,1370,476,500]" name="Maldives" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Maldive Islands</collectingCountry>
illustrated in color by 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[348,803,511,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Randall, J. E. &amp; R. C. Anderson (1993) Annotated checklist of the epipelagic and shore fishes of the Maldive Islands. Ichthyological Bulletin 59, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1993">
Randall &amp; Anderson (
<number box="[595,654,511,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="1993.0">1993</number>
, pl. 
<number box="[701,716,511,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="5.0">5</number>
, fig. H)
</bibRefCitation>
provides a link between the subadult of 
<figureCitation box="[1254,1348,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1776,1799]" captionTargetBox="[189,1409,942,1754]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1410,942,1754]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Bodianus bimaculatus, subadult, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia (R. Field)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
Figure 
<number box="[1334,1348,511,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
and the initial-phase adult in 
<bibRefCitation author="Gomon" box="[388,557,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Gomon, M. F. (2006) A revision of the labrid fish genus Bodianus. Records of the Australian Museum, suppl. 30, 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="2006">
Gomon (
<number box="[487,549,548,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName box="[151,400,584,608]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Labridae" genus="Bodianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimaculatus">
<emphasis box="[151,400,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Bodianus bimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from depths of 
<number box="[686,714,583,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="20.0">20</number>
to more than 
<quantity box="[867,926,583,607]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="60.0">60 m</quantity>
, generally deeper than 
<specimenCount box="[1184,1248,583,607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1184,1244,583,607]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
It is the smallest species of the genus, with females maturing at 
<quantity box="[675,730,620,644]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
SL (
<bibRefCitation author="Gomon" box="[785,946,620,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" refString="Gomon, M. F. (2006) A revision of the labrid fish genus Bodianus. Records of the Australian Museum, suppl. 30, 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="2006">
Gomon, 
<number box="[885,946,620,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
